originalText: pir_flinger
Start Element
flinger
Leave me alone.
context.npc_xpbl_pir_flinger_notTalking
By d' sea - dis cannot be! Dis cannot be!
context.npc_xpbl_pir_flinger_startedThrowOff
'Ey, banga. $(context.player.Name), right? I'm D' Flinger. Cap'n sent ye?
Well, I never... I've been 'roun' Hell's Gut fer a lon' time an' never thought I'd actually see anyone go pay dat spooky hospital a visit. So, ruin-crawler, wha's up?
I noticed Calamity's menu's gotten a whole lot, hmmm, richer since we started raidin' again. Didn' realize how much I missed imported goods, te-he.
English
Aegis is toast, yea.
Wha's it?
Wha' is it?
Whatcha wan', dumbat?
Wha'?
Who's the best now, banga?
Yer good, banga, real good.
Ye ain' bad, banga, ain' bad at all.
Ye can obviously throw a blade, banga. But dat wasn' even close, no, no.
Ahahahahahaha....
Dis is gettin' pathetic.
Mhm. To check on the prisoner.
Yes. To see if you got rid of the professor's corpse.
English
Busy day fer everyone today, ain' it? Dere goes d' Profman, ye took a coupla-kilometa-deep dive, I ate dis monstrous crab an' shroom sandwich. Life's a fight, ain' it, te-he, ain' it?
I thought I'd never see yer face again, banga. It ain' every day sumone gits to take a coupla-kilometas-deep dive, ye know.
Now we jus' need d' Scalers to settle an' we're jettin', banga.
Git jetted.

::The muttering that follows is composed of numerous juicy-sounding swears; how juicy they actually are is something both his accent and low voice fail to deliver. Nevertheless, he hands you the charons you won fair and square.::

Dere...
context.npc_xpbl_pir_flinger_playersThrowingSkill
But I'm better.
I'm d' bes'. I'm *D'* *Flinger*.
Jus'... stop, banga. Stop.
'E's okay. Complains from time to time 'bout d' bugs an' sum nasty itchin' - oh, an' d' stench - but otherwise 'e's okay.
::He nods.:: Dumped 'is corpse down d' manhole.
Yea. Well dis place is pretty self-explanatory, tehehe.
::[Throwing]:: I'd like to challenge you to a throw off. We'll use that dartboard over there.
I want a rematch.
Why D' Flinger?
English
I'm here to check on the prisoner.
English
Did you get rid of the professor's corpse?
What is under that manhole in the middle of the room?
Tell me about Thrasher.
I've found the Thrasher. It's a giant hermit crab.
Wanna hear a joke?
Do you torture people here?
Gotta run. See ya.
No one lef' to bug us 'bout Profman's sendin' unda, te-he-he.
When ye think about it, we did Profman a favor, te-he-he.
Wit' d' way things've turned out, Profman shoulda stayed wit' us, te-he-he. It woulda been a lot healthier fer 'im.
Can you come closer, please? There's something I want to talk to you about.
Do you... torture people here?
I'm hungry.
Let me out.
Let me out or I'll slaughter all of you sons of rats one by one, as slowly and as painfully as possible!
Hey there, handsome.
How about you and I make a deal? I've got money. Lots of it. And loot you wouldn't believe.
::[Dexterity] Grab the keys hanging by his belt.::
::[Melee] or [Strength] Grab his head and smash it against the bars.::
English
::[Melee] Shiv him.::
::Spit on him.::
::Attack!::
Leave me.
Ye lost. 'S been fun takin' yer coins, tehe.

::He grabs his belly and bends forward.::

Aaaaaaahahahahaha...
Oh, an' also 'bout us Jetters bein' animals an' how we should let 'im go. Tehehe. Dumbat.
That's wha' ye git when ye start beatin' like derailed. Cap'n was really jettin' pissed 'bout ye sendin' 'im unda. 'E could've been real useful, d' prof.
A *fling* off! An' ye fer real, banga? Ye sure ye wanna go up agains' d' bes'? *Dee* bes'? I don' like seein' grown folks cry, tehehe.
Another fling off? Ain' ye had enough?
'Cuz I'm d' bes' blade flinga aroun'. Fer real. I *especially* like provin' it to dryfoots who jus' joined an' think dey're d' bes' jetters around.

Dis? ::He points at the aforementioned.:: Dere's a small cave down dere. We use it to dump garbage, waste, an occasional corpse... Feedin' d' Thrasher, as we like sayin', tehe. An' dem toilets over dere, yea, in d' cells, dey flush straight down into it as well.

No one knows fer sure wha' it is. Folks been hearin' noises comin' from below d' ground, sounds o' sumthin' big movin' and thrashin' about - 'ence d' name Thrasher. It probably eats all d' crap we throw down dere, but I don' know how it manages to survive d' toxic gases an' all dat.
Ye seen it? Fer real? 'Ermit crab? Well... makes sense. Wha's it like?
Huh? A j-- A joke? Okay. Okay. I'm all ears. Tell me a joke.
Go ahead.

Ye saw d' blood an' crap on d' floor, huh? ::Without breaking eye contact he reaches for his knives, pulling one out slowly. He raises it to about a forearm's length away from his face, in line with his nose and dead center between his eyes. He turns it around leisurely, producing almost hypnotic glinting, but behind the flashes there hides a baleful grin in the background.::

Hehe...
flinger_close
Ye ain' tryina seduce me, huh?
Alright, alright. Jus' don' try anythin' funky.
I can hear ye well enough from 'ere.
Ye got a bowl behind ye - knock yerself out, te-he-he.
No. Ye an' Profman stayin' locked up til Cap'n says ye go. Now, go free or go unda? *Dat* we'll see, yea. Te-he.
Ye ain' gunna do nuthin', clod. Now shut yer traps or Imma pop yer sorry ass. I can fling a blade right between dem bars, ye dig. ::He turns around and leaves.::
Mm. Whatcha wan'?

Look, banga, I got yer money an' yer loot upstairs already. An' since I got d' key, I can always "borrow" anythin' I need, if ye catch d' way me jet's floatin'. Ain' no one checked wha' ye had before yer ass ended up in 'ere, ye dig.

::As swift as a snake striking its prey, you pluck the keys dangling from his belt before he realized what's happening. When that moment of realization does come, however, he reaches through the bars in an attempt to snatch them back, but you prove quicker yet again: You lock his arm against the bars with one hand - immobilizing him temporarily - all the while unlocking the door with your other hand, displaying a feat of great ambidexterity.::

::As swift as a snake - one that suffers from cataracts and from having been run over by a quad bike - striking its prey, you try grabbing the keys dangling from the jailer's belt. You fail, obviously. He recoils, then growls at you.::

HEY, HEY! Ye really wan' a blade between yer eyes, ye slimy clod! If I hear ye breathin' d' wrong way, if I see ye eyein' dem keys again - if I even dream ye tryina file down d' lock on dem doors over dere - Imma sen' ye unda, $(#boy/girl), ye dig? Ye dig, clod?
::You whisper a few unintelligible words, and the big guy instinctively leans forward. ::

::He tries to dodge it, but you still manage to hit his left cheek. He wipes the spit off with his palm before surprising you by returning the favor with even greater accuracy. You remove his phlegm from your eyes, opening them only to see him grinning with amusement.::

Ye ain' gunna outspit me, banga. I've had "exchanges" wit' d' prisoners ye'd never believe. Now keep yer mouth shut or d' nex' thin' flyin' at yer face is gunna be one o' me blades. Yea, blades.
Ye stay put in dere, dig?

::His stare is such that it could pin you to that very dartboard you threw your knives at.::

Yer... ::He finally utters.::
::Leave without saying anything.::
Ah... ah... ah... Ye sss-- Tehehe...
Whatever. I could always use more coins.
Tehehehe. I remember dis one kid, sum clod from Junkyard dat cried when I beat 'im. Kid was delusional. Dat also got 'im killed a week later. Clod.
We don' raise d' man'ole unless we're dumpin' sumthin', 'cuz not only will d' reek rise up but dere's toxic gases from sum o' d' stuff we dropped, ye know. Ye, ye don' touch it, dig?
I know what it is - a giant hermit crab.
*Dead*.

Nah. I jus' beat dem up if need be, maybe break a bone or two if dem bangas earned it. Or just pop 'em an' dump 'em thru dat manhole. I mean, I love flingin' me blades, but I ain' no man-butcherin' psycho.
::Wait for him to approach.::
::[Persuade]:: It'd be easier on my voice if you'd come closer. Your pal punched me in the throat so hard... ugh... it hurts when I... speak.
Ahhh... Ye'll get yer chomp when it's time.
::You manage to unlock the door a moment before he liberates himself from your hold.::

Bastar'.

::He leaves.::
::Meanwhile, you reach for your weapon...::
::You swiftly reach for his long mustache and yank on them with everything you've got.::
wep.shiv
Dig.
::Say nothing.::
...d' bes'.
Leave. me.
::He replies with a scornful glance.::
::His valediction - a scornful glance.::
Dat was jettin', banga. ::He wipes away the tears.:: Fer real.
Should've, yea.
Accident or not, d' guy's unda now.
Ye watch dat tongue o' yers. Ye piss me off an' Imma pin it to yer lower jaw wit' one o' me blades, ye dig?
I'll bet you twenty charons.
English
I'll bet you fifty charons.
English
I'll bet you a hundred charons.
English
I'll bet you two hundred charons.
English
I'll bet you three hundred charons.
English
I'll bet you four hundred charons.
English
I'll bet you five hundred charons.
Thrasher? You mean that giant hermit crab?

Dunno. Maybe it's a crab o' sum kind. It sounds fairly slow when it's movin', so it ain' a creeper. An' creepers are always in groups anyway. An', heh, dey can clim' walls. But I dunno. Could be anythin'.
Wha'd ye do? When ye saw it?
By d' sea! Wha'did ye do?
Yer full o' it. I didn' hear nuthin'. I hear dat thin' takin' a crap an' yer tellin' me ye fought it without me noticin' anythin'?
I did hear lotsa noise down dere...
A rathound walks into a bar... and the barkeeper shoots it! ::Laugh.:: Get it?
What does a cell about to undergo mitosis say to an interested geneticist? "I hope I have your divided attention!"
::[Intelligence]:: What has five legs, two arms and a single eye?
Actually, I don't know any good jokes.
That's all I've got.
::He sheathes the knife.::
Xpbl_E3_FlingerApproaches
Cruzer's... got a heavy hand, yea. Alright den, alright...
Den it's bes' ye don' speak, banga. It ain' gunna hurt dat way, is it now? Jus' sit dere an' be quiet.
Ye... ye stop botherin' me wit' nonsense, dumbat.
Ye underwire got broken an' ye need sumone to fix it? Hahahaha!
Oh, an' ye wan' sum fun, girl? Well - ye ain' gunna git no fun!
Ye, I can pop ye between d' eyes thru dem bars, girl.
Ye suck at dis, girl. Stop. I see what yer tryina do, an' it ain' gunna work. Although... I gotta say I am proud of me 'dominal beast 'ere, hehe.
Listen, girl:
If I let ye go, right? Heh. Get outta 'ere-- Em, I mean shut up an' stop makin' it worse fer yerself. Dis ain' gunna do ye any good.
I never forget anythin', banga.

::[Eviscerate] You grab onto his knife strap and tug the big fellow into the bars - and right into the rusty tip of your shiv. You drive it into his belly button: The pain debilitates him, and the unwieldy position he's in prevents him from breaking free or retaliating, at least not fast enough. And as he struggles, the dull blade sinks into his abdomen, your hand guiding it deeper and deeper in a fashion more akin to sawing than cutting, until more than half of your forearm is inside.::

::You grab onto his knife strap and tug the big fellow into the bars - so you could drive your shiv into the left side of his neck, just beside the larynx. You start sawing outward with your dull blade, through his blood vessels and against the blood gushing from them. In his eyes you see the reflection of your blood-spattered face, jaw clenched and eyes gravely focused, yet at the same time, in the same reflection, you could also see a knife of his own nearing a neck - of your own.::

::You grab onto his knife strap and tug the big fellow into the bars. But as you try stabbing into his neck with your shiv, you accidentally hit one of the bars and it deflects your blade. Your error allows him to move back, pulling you into the bars instead. 

Outstretched, and with your shoulder jammed between the bars, you let go...::

::His face slams against the bars, allowing you to grab his head with your other hand so that you may better introduce his skull to solid metal - again and again and again. This skull, however, proves far too thick for you to break before running out of stamina, so you give him one final slam before grabbing the keys dangling from his belt and pushing him away from the door.::

::His face slams against the bars, but your plan turns sour the moment you try grabbing his gleaming bald head with both of your hands. It slips from your grasp, and your jailer leaps backward. You can no longer reach him, whereas the knives he's pulling out can most certainly reach you.::
Wha's done is done.
Now, is dat all ye wanted or was dere sumthin' else?
Twenty. Ye kiddin' me? Ye got so little faith in yer skills? Tehe.
Fifty? Okay. Could use extra fifty.
context.npc_xpbl_pir_flinger_charonsBet
Hundred. Fer real.
Dat's sum jettin' coin.
Ye wan' more?
Three? Jettin', jettin'.
Ye sure, banga? I love coins, don' get me wron', but I wouldn' wanna see ye send yerself under fer losin' all yer savin's. It ain' good fer d' Jetters.
Dis again...
Wise decision, banga. Tehehehe...
Yea. Thrasher.
Git outta 'ere. Lyin' bastar'.

I ain' gonna hear dat thin' thrash about no more, I guess. 

So lon' Thrasher. Never got to taste ye, but ye probably tasted like crap anyway. Tehehe.
Tehehe... hehe... hahahahaha! Filthy rats! Drown d' vermin. Der place ain' in no bars, or dis world fer dat matter.
Whaaaaaaaaaa'? Wha's m-mutosis? Sumthin' to do with dem mutie freaks, huh?
Huh... Ain' got a clue.
Eh... yea... Jettin'.
Dat's okay, banga.
Eh... Alright.
Now, ye try any funky stuff an' yer gunna git sum o' dat I mentioned, ye dig.
Now, now, dat stuff ain' gunna work on me, girl.
Don' think I don' know what yer tryina do 'ere. It ain' gunna work.

We got 'ere plenty a floozin' girls to keep all us boys... clear-headed, hehe. Fine, fine girls. Ye ain' nuthin' special, hun, an' ye better knock it off an' keep quiet or Imma dispense sum punishmen' on yer sorry ass.
key.xpbl_e3_jail
::Fight!::
Eviscerate

::You pull everything out: shiv, hand, guts and blood - plenty of blood. He slides down the bars and to his knees, holding onto what he can with what fleeting strength he has.

You must've hit some major blood vessels, because he perishes quickly.::
::But then he closes his eyes and slides down the bars, gurgling and dropping his unused blade; it takes a few seconds more before he perishes in a pool of his own blood.::
::Fight!::
Place a real bet.
Ye got it, banga - le's flin'. We'll be usin' *my* blades.
Oh... I can' resis' takin' coins from delusional folks. I jus'...
Wounded it so that I could retreat safely.
Pfft. Killed it.
Dat's a good one, banga. Gonna remember it fer sure.
Dat's a good one. Imma remember dat. It ain' gunna help ye one bit, now, but it's a good one.

I... I don' get it. Must be one of 'em fancy jokes fer folks who think dey're smar' an' stuff. Me, I like dem dirty, *greasy* jokes, ye know, like d' one about d' quakin' nurse from d' North, tehe... hehe... So if ye know sumthin' like dat, yea, dat's wha' I like.
::Start the fling off and give it your best.::
English
::[Intelligence] Start the fling off but lose intentionally.::

::[Mercantile]:: Don't you worry about my financial status, Flinger. I'm more than good. But even if I weren't it wouldn't matter anyway: You won't get to see any of my money 'cause you are going to lose, mate.
::[Intimidate]:: You scared you're going to lose your coins, *banga*?
Dryfoot. Tehehehe. Ran like a little pansy, tehe.
Good thin' ye still got to keep yer head. Even regular 'ermits can be a pain in the ass, let alone dis one.
By d' sea... Well, at leas'
Tehehe... ::He counts his fingers.:: hehe...
Tehehe... I gets it. Brutal. Tehehe...
::End Dialog.::
English
English
Me? Hahahaha. Ye clearly don' dig nuthin', banga. Ye really are a dryfoot.
English
Tehehe...
Ah, jus' messin' wit' ye.
Dere ain' no shame in retreatin' if it's justified, banga. Sum things jus' ain' worth it.
Hahahahahaha! It be true! Ye cheeky bastar'. If Razor hears ye, yer gunna git a bloody grin from ear to ear.
Ye fer real, banga? Ye are fer real. Ye really are.
Imma be nice an' let ye reconsider, okay? Yea...
::His expression turns serious.:: Ye mean it. Ye think yer dat tough, don'cha? I ain' scared of ye, I ain' scared of no one. No one.

Hehe... an' at first I thought it was gunna be sum mangled crab or sumethin'. 

Tehe...
Tehehehe. Jettin'. Dere are better Lurker jokes out dere, though, like the one wit' d'... tehehe... wit' d' chewy zoner - dat one's jettin'! But dis one ain' bad.
xpbl_e3_down
Ain' bad at all. Tehe...
